01:01.166 --> 01:03.624
(INHALES DEEPLY) Okay.

01:03.625 --> 01:07.916
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

01:07.917 --> 01:10.582
Good morning.
Good morning, Sabrina.

01:10.583 --> 01:12.332
Hi, Mrs. Reese.
It's so nice to see you again.

01:12.333 --> 01:15.124
You too. I'm excited
to see what you've prepared.

01:15.125 --> 01:17.040
Okay.

01:17.041 --> 01:19.708
The furniture's
sleek lines balance

01:19.709 --> 01:22.207
the curve of
the natural elements.

01:22.208 --> 01:24.791
I don't see my family's
heirloom throw pillows.

01:24.792 --> 01:26.040
Where are those going to go?

01:26.041 --> 01:28.374
Well, look
at the aesthetic clarity.

01:28.375 --> 01:30.416
It's much cleaner
and more balanced

01:30.417 --> 01:31.666
without the additional throw.

01:31.667 --> 01:33.124
I just don't see
the unique elements

01:33.125 --> 01:34.749
of this design of yours.

01:34.750 --> 01:36.958
The couch is already
a statement piece.

01:36.959 --> 01:38.999
I see.

01:39.000 --> 01:42.040
Sabrina, can I speak
with you privately?

01:42.041 --> 01:43.791
Of course.

01:43.792 --> 01:45.291
Can you give us a few minutes?

01:48.333 --> 01:51.332
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

01:51.333 --> 01:58.250
(MUSIC PLAYING)

02:04.333 --> 02:06.333
Olivia?

02:14.417 --> 02:18.040
Nobody wants you
to succeed more than I do.

02:18.041 --> 02:21.290
But these designs,
they're textbook.

02:21.291 --> 02:23.207
Where is your
unique point of view?

02:23.208 --> 02:26.499
What makes this
an Olivia Wilson original?

02:26.500 --> 02:29.249
Well, I... I always
include the white shag rug.

02:29.250 --> 02:30.791
I mean, that's kind
of my signature.

02:30.792 --> 02:32.749
Olivia, you have so much talent,

02:32.750 --> 02:36.332
but bottom line,
these designs lack heart.

02:36.333 --> 02:38.791
A good designer
follows the rules.

02:38.792 --> 02:41.958
A great designer puts
a little piece of herself

02:41.959 --> 02:44.416
into every single detail.

02:44.417 --> 02:47.249
This is not about being perfect.

02:47.250 --> 02:49.791
It's about being fearless.

02:49.792 --> 02:52.791
I'm sorry, but I really think
that the biggest gift

02:52.792 --> 02:56.250
that I can give you
is forcing you to move on.

02:59.583 --> 03:02.417
Please keep in touch. I do want
to see where you're at.

03:06.542 --> 03:09.582
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

03:09.583 --> 03:16.500
(MUSIC PLAYING)

03:18.000 --> 03:24.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:26.583 --> 03:33.500
(MUSIC PLAYING)

03:49.792 --> 03:53.165
What are you doing here?
Did you forget something?

03:53.166 --> 03:57.165
You all right?

03:57.166 --> 04:00.583
I got fired.
What?

04:05.834 --> 04:07.582
Okay.

04:07.583 --> 04:09.500
You gonna be all right?

04:18.500 --> 04:19.999
What's that?

04:20.000 --> 04:24.666
It's my dad's 25th work
anniversary party this Saturday.

04:24.667 --> 04:27.874
I wanted to go,
but I-I thought I would be here

04:27.875 --> 04:30.666
decorating Mrs. Reese's
apartment this weekend.

04:30.667 --> 04:32.791
Spend some time
with your family.

04:32.792 --> 04:35.708
It ll be good for you.

04:35.709 --> 04:39.249
Yeah, I think I just need
to organize my thoughts.

04:39.250 --> 04:42.208
I think you need
a break from organizing.

04:45.667 --> 04:48.040
Thanks.

04:48.041 --> 04:50.708
Feel better, okay?

04:50.709 --> 04:56.124
I'm here if you need me.

04:56.125 --> 04:59.040
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

