<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

05:38.000 --> 05:41.958
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

05:41.959 --> 05:43.916
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

05:43.917 --> 05:47.916
<i>♪ Oh
yeah yeah ♪</i>

05:47.917 --> 05:50.834
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

05:58.000 --> 06:01.290
Hi. Can I help you?
Hi.

06:01.291 --> 06:05.416
I, uh... I'm Olivia Wilson.
I'm Neil's daughter.

06:05.417 --> 06:08.708
Oh, I was beginning to think
you were an urban myth.

06:08.709 --> 06:10.499
Neil talks about you
all the time.

06:10.500 --> 06:13.249
Um, Scott Norrell, crew leader.

06:13.250 --> 06:14.457
Nice to meet you.

06:14.458 --> 06:16.249
So you been working
for my Dad for a while?

06:16.250 --> 06:18.499
Yeah, a while, yeah. I worked
for another moving company

06:18.500 --> 06:20.958
just south of here for
a couple months after college.

06:20.959 --> 06:23.124
I guess I've been so caught up
with work I have no idea

06:23.125 --> 06:25.082
what's going on around here.

06:25.083 --> 06:26.290
Well, I'll be darned.

06:26.291 --> 06:27.999
Hello, angel.

06:28.000 --> 06:30.165
Hi.
Good to see you.

06:30.166 --> 06:31.166
I see you met Scott.

06:31.167 --> 06:32.708
Yeah.
Look who it is.

06:32.709 --> 06:35.708
Hi.
Hey. You in town for a while?

06:35.709 --> 06:37.666
Yeah, just came for the party.
Your Dad can't stop

06:37.667 --> 06:39.833
talking about you,
his New York designer.

06:39.834 --> 06:41.666
Karen's gonna be super
pumped to see you.

06:41.667 --> 06:45.040
Oh, I can't wait to see her.
Is my Dad around here?

06:45.041 --> 06:46.499
Yeah, he's in there.
He's doing stuff.

06:46.500 --> 06:48.332
Okay. I'm gonna go say hi.

06:48.333 --> 06:51.332
(SOFT MUSIC)

06:51.333 --> 06:58.291
(MUSIC PLAYING)

06:59.417 --> 07:01.332
Are you kidding me?

07:01.333 --> 07:03.165
My baby girl.

07:03.166 --> 07:06.249
Hi, Dad. How are you?
I'm great.

07:06.250 --> 07:07.916
I brought you this.
What is this?

07:07.917 --> 07:10.374
Oh, it's for 25 years
of business,

07:10.375 --> 07:12.541
just a bunch of little
knickknacks from New York.

07:12.542 --> 07:14.541
Would you look at that?
Thank you.

07:14.542 --> 07:17.833
Okay, let me see. Let me see.
Okay, it's perfection.

07:17.834 --> 07:19.666
Thankfully, you look like
your mother.

07:19.667 --> 07:21.165
I just don't know
how you're here.

07:21.166 --> 07:23.749
This is crazy. You're so busy.
You're a big designer.

07:23.750 --> 07:26.249
All that's going on, and have I
told you how proud I am of you?

07:26.250 --> 07:28.624
Okay, look, I'm closing up.
Let's go home.

07:28.625 --> 07:29.916
I'm gonna make some lasagna

07:29.917 --> 07:31.374
cause you look like you
need something to eat.

07:31.375 --> 07:33.207
Lasagna?
Lasagna.

07:33.208 --> 07:34.958
I just didn't know
you knew how to cook.

07:34.959 --> 07:38.582
Well, things change, right?

07:38.583 --> 07:43.916
Oh, I can't believe you're here.
This is incredible.

07:43.917 --> 07:45.040
(PHONE RINGING)

07:45.041 --> 07:46.582
Robinator, talk to me, buddy.

07:46.583 --> 07:48.290
What's up?
I don't know.

07:48.291 --> 07:51.124
I'm a little worried about
alienating the neighborhood.

07:51.125 --> 07:52.541
Just think about the money.

07:52.542 --> 07:54.374
Is it even worth
setting up shop here?

07:54.375 --> 07:57.416
Look, I'm gonna pretend you
didn't just say that, all right?

07:57.417 --> 07:59.249
Now, your work is not done
until we have driven out

07:59.250 --> 08:01.040
every single independent mover

08:01.041 --> 08:03.082
in Southern California,
you got it?

08:03.083 --> 08:04.916
Yes, sir.
Perfect.

08:04.917 --> 08:06.249
Now, who's the main competition?

08:06.250 --> 08:09.582
Wilson Family Movers,
been here forever.

08:09.583 --> 08:10.791
You know, it's no biggie.

08:10.792 --> 08:13.165
You're gonna drive them
into the ground, man.

08:13.166 --> 08:15.290
I got a meeting
with the owner tomorrow.

08:15.291 --> 08:16.708
Good.

08:16.709 --> 08:18.582
You know, there might be a spot
for you at the home office.

08:18.583 --> 08:21.249
I know you'd like that.
All right, man, I got to dash.

08:21.250 --> 08:22.916
I'll... I'll catch you
on the flipside.

08:22.917 --> 08:24.834
(DIAL TONE)

08:29.417 --> 08:32.375
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

08:33.667 --> 08:35.707
Hey, Karen.
Hey. What up?

08:35.708 --> 08:39.332
What's up, buddy? So you, uh,
score any online dates today?

08:39.332 --> 08:42.499
Nope. We're gonna have
to exchange war stories.

08:42.500 --> 08:43.874
Wow, that bad?

08:43.875 --> 08:47.165
Oh, worse than
you can even imagine.

08:47.166 --> 08:49.499
It is rough out there.
Hard to find love these days.

08:49.500 --> 08:51.499
Well, at least you love
your job, right?

08:51.500 --> 08:53.290
Wait, I thought you liked
working at E&K Fabrics.

08:53.291 --> 08:55.457
Well, I'm a receptionist, right?

08:55.458 --> 08:56.833
I love textiles,

08:56.834 --> 08:59.749
but all they ever want me
to do is answer the phones.

08:59.750 --> 09:02.040
Why don't we work
on your online profile thing?

09:02.041 --> 09:03.374
Yeah? You'd do that?

09:03.375 --> 09:07.374
Why not?
Here.

09:07.375 --> 09:08.499
All right, we're gonna have
to change your

09:08.500 --> 09:09.958
"What I'm looking for" section.

09:09.959 --> 09:12.416
Why?
"Someone who isn't creepy?"

09:12.417 --> 09:14.791
What?
Exactly. That's exactly right.

09:14.792 --> 09:16.791
So let me see what kind
of damage control I can do here.

09:16.792 --> 09:18.249
Okay, yeah.

09:18.250 --> 09:20.624
"No one with complicated
facial hair.

09:20.625 --> 09:22.332
Must have all of their teeth."

09:22.333 --> 09:24.708
Yummy grilled cheese
is what you like?

09:24.709 --> 09:27.667
That's not bad.
Not bad? Right.

09:30.625 --> 09:32.999
(SIGHS)

09:33.000 --> 09:35.165
Mmm, this lasagna is good.

09:35.166 --> 09:36.749
Mm-hmm.
I'm impressed.

09:36.750 --> 09:40.833
(CHUCKLES)
So you been exercising?

09:40.834 --> 09:42.374
Not as much as you would
like me to be,

09:42.375 --> 09:46.290
but I swear I have started
hiking on the weekends.

09:46.291 --> 09:49.958
And how about you? Um, oh, boy,
you were seeing that guy, Dave...

09:49.959 --> 09:51.165
Garrett?
Garrett.

09:51.166 --> 09:53.541
No, no, that ended a while ago.

09:53.542 --> 09:56.499
Oh, I'm sorry.
Yeah.

09:56.500 --> 09:57.791
Well, how's work?

09:57.792 --> 09:59.666
Um, well, it's, um...

09:59.667 --> 10:02.040
Honey, I know I probably
don't say it enough,

10:02.041 --> 10:05.124
but I am just so proud of you.
Thanks.

10:05.125 --> 10:07.416
So tell me, how long
are you here for?

10:07.417 --> 10:09.040
A while. Is... is that okay?

10:09.041 --> 10:11.791
Sweetie, I love having
you here, absolutely.

10:11.792 --> 10:16.040
I just wish I had known as far
as I planned that fishing trip.

10:16.041 --> 10:18.332
Oh, your annual guy
fishing trip, right?

10:18.333 --> 10:19.999
That's the one.
You have to go.

10:20.000 --> 10:21.916
No, I don't.
I... I can cancel.

10:21.917 --> 10:24.124
Dad, you would have so much fun,

10:24.125 --> 10:25.874
and plus I could stay here
and help with the company.

10:25.875 --> 10:27.499
Pl... is that how you
want to relax?

10:27.500 --> 10:31.624
Working relaxes me.
Which I've never understood.

10:31.625 --> 10:33.416
I mean, if you want,
you can, you know,

10:33.417 --> 10:34.791
come with me
to the office tomorrow.

10:34.792 --> 10:36.999
Mm, yes, Dad.

10:37.000 --> 10:38.374
I will come
into the office tomorrow.

10:38.375 --> 10:41.791
Okay.

10:41.792 --> 10:44.791
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC)

10:44.792 --> 10:51.750
(MUSIC PLAYING)

10:55.834 --> 10:57.750
(SIGHS)

11:00.625 --> 11:02.624
Hmm.

11:02.625 --> 11:07.082
(MUSIC PLAYING)

11:07.083 --> 11:09.082
I miss you.

11:09.083 --> 11:16.041
(MUSIC PLAYING)

11:31.041 --> 11:33.959
(PHONE RINGING)

11:36.750 --> 11:39.290
Hey.
Hey, how was your flight?

11:39.291 --> 11:43.249
I slept, ate some peanuts.

11:43.250 --> 11:46.124
That's the spirit.
How are things?

11:46.125 --> 11:49.207
Hard.
With my Mom gone

11:49.208 --> 11:51.666
I just didn't have the guts
to tell my Dad I was fired.

11:51.667 --> 11:54.874
He's just so proud of me.

11:54.875 --> 11:56.958
I don't want to disappoint him.

11:56.959 --> 12:00.249
I'm sure he would be proud
of you no matter what.

12:00.250 --> 12:04.541
I got your list of how to keep
things tidy around here.

12:04.542 --> 12:08.290
I plan on completely
forgetting it even exists.

12:08.291 --> 12:10.333
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

12:13.875 --> 12:15.834
Hi, guys.

12:18.041 --> 12:19.374
Is my Dad here?

12:19.375 --> 12:20.499
Uh, no, no, no,

12:20.500 --> 12:22.082
he just... he had
to run to a quick meeting,

12:22.083 --> 12:23.916
but he said that you'd be
helping us move today?

12:23.917 --> 12:25.666
Oh, no, I was actually
just gonna stay here

12:25.667 --> 12:26.791
and do some paperwork.

12:26.792 --> 12:28.082
That's what I used to do.

12:28.083 --> 12:31.165
We could really use your help.
Okay.

12:31.166 --> 12:34.332
Great.

12:34.333 --> 12:36.291
Meet us back here in five.

12:40.333 --> 12:42.332
Are you serious?

12:42.333 --> 12:45.332
(UPBEAT MUSIC)

12:45.333 --> 12:52.374
(MUSIC PLAYING)

12:52.375 --> 12:53.708
You ready?

12:53.709 --> 12:56.582
Actually, I used to stay
in the office with my Mom.

12:56.583 --> 12:58.708
So this is your first move?
No, I just haven't done it

12:58.709 --> 13:00.374
in a really long time.
What do we do?

13:00.375 --> 13:02.207
We pack up everything,
and we move it.

13:02.208 --> 13:04.541
No, I know that, but, like,
where do we...

13:04.542 --> 13:09.582
Watch your back.
Start?

13:09.583 --> 13:13.624
<i>♪ Ooh, baby ♪</i>

13:13.625 --> 13:15.040
<i>♪ You got me feeling
something new ♪</i>

13:15.041 --> 13:17.249
It doesn't have to be perfect.

13:17.250 --> 13:19.332
It's all about efficiency.

13:19.333 --> 13:21.874
<i>♪ Ooh, darling ♪</i>

13:21.875 --> 13:26.874
<i>♪ I got to figure out
what to do ♪</i>

13:26.875 --> 13:30.207
<i>♪ I'm desperate so far away ♪</i>

13:30.208 --> 13:32.250
<i>♪ Trying to get back something
that's been yesterday ♪</i>

13:34.333 --> 13:36.833
<i>♪ No more sitting here crying ♪</i>

13:36.834 --> 13:38.624
<i>♪ In my bed ♪</i>

13:38.625 --> 13:41.791
<i>♪ Trying to figure out
what to say ♪</i>

13:41.792 --> 13:43.749
<i>♪ Believe it or not ♪</i>

13:43.750 --> 13:46.249
<i>♪ Ooh, oh, baby ♪</i>

13:46.250 --> 13:51.249
<i>♪ Believe it or not ♪</i>
(GRUNTS, SIGHS)

13:51.250 --> 13:54.749
I am impressed.
Good rally.

13:54.750 --> 13:56.082
<i>♪ Believe it or not ♪</i>
Mm.

13:56.083 --> 13:58.249
<i>♪ Ooh, baby ♪</i>

13:58.250 --> 14:00.666
(CHUCKLES)

14:00.667 --> 14:03.082
(LIGHT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

14:03.083 --> 14:04.374
Thank you.

14:04.375 --> 14:06.457
Uh, excuse me, Mr. Fuller?

14:06.458 --> 14:08.666
Yeah? Mr. Neil Wilson?
Yes.

14:08.667 --> 14:10.207
Hey, it's a pleasure
to meet you.

14:10.208 --> 14:12.249
Please have a seat.

14:12.250 --> 14:13.416
Can I get you
something to drink?

14:13.417 --> 14:16.582
Oh, no, thank you.
What is this about?

14:16.583 --> 14:18.749
Well, it's just such an honor
to meet you.

14:18.750 --> 14:21.040
I've heard so much
about Wilson Family Movers.

14:21.041 --> 14:22.833
Everything you've done here
in the community,

14:22.834 --> 14:24.332
it's really remarkable.

14:24.333 --> 14:27.290
You guys have been here for...
for how long, 25 years?

14:27.291 --> 14:28.791
That's right.
That is a long time

14:28.792 --> 14:30.624
for a local business.

14:30.625 --> 14:32.457
We really value
that kind of commitment.

14:32.458 --> 14:34.958
You know, I appreciate
your kind words, Mr. Fuller,

14:34.959 --> 14:38.624
but I'm just not sure
where you're going with this.

14:38.625 --> 14:43.457
Well, I have some good news.

14:43.458 --> 14:46.332
Acme is in a very rare position
right now.

14:46.333 --> 14:48.082
We have the means

14:48.083 --> 14:50.290
to make very generous offers

14:50.291 --> 14:52.249
to smaller businesses,

14:52.250 --> 14:55.332
and we would like to
buy Wilson Family Movers.

14:55.333 --> 14:58.332
Well, I'm not looking to sell,
and Acme,

14:58.333 --> 14:59.833
it seems like a-a fine company,

14:59.834 --> 15:03.082
but, well, Wilson Movers,

15:03.083 --> 15:04.499
well, we're a family outfit.

15:04.500 --> 15:06.999
And look,
I understand that, really.

15:07.000 --> 15:12.249
I do, but small companies like
yours are losing the market.

15:12.250 --> 15:16.499
Consumers only care
about speed and convenience.

15:16.500 --> 15:19.833
The family feel is just not
so important to them

15:19.834 --> 15:22.541
when it comes to moving.

15:22.542 --> 15:26.999
Look, Neil, just hit me
with a number.

15:27.000 --> 15:28.999
Mr. Fuller, you should
come to our 25th

15:29.000 --> 15:30.958
anniversary party tonight.

15:30.959 --> 15:37.374
I think you will see why
Wilson Movers is here to stay.

15:37.375 --> 15:39.375
Goodbye, Mr. Fuller.

15:42.542 --> 15:44.457
One down, one to go.

15:44.458 --> 15:47.457
(UPBEAT MUSIC)

15:47.458 --> 15:53.791
(MUSIC PLAYING)

15:53.792 --> 15:56.332
Thank you.

15:56.333 --> 15:58.416
Hey, can I see the clipboard?

15:58.417 --> 16:00.666
Who else are we moving today?

16:00.667 --> 16:02.124
Mrs. Norrell.

16:02.125 --> 16:05.041
Yup, we're moving my grandma.

16:08.709 --> 16:13.791
I know, I-I said I would,
but I'm still not ready,

16:13.792 --> 16:16.709
and, um, I'm sorry
to be an inconvenience.

16:19.542 --> 16:21.290
Grandma, you don't have
to do anything.

16:21.291 --> 16:24.958
We're gonna make it
really easy for you.

16:24.959 --> 16:26.791
It's not that.
You live

16:26.792 --> 16:28.582
in this big house by yourself.

16:28.583 --> 16:30.749
It's hard for you to get around.

16:30.750 --> 16:33.082
We have this amazing place
at Golden Meadows.

16:33.083 --> 16:37.000
You know, I promise you you ll
feel more comfortable there.

16:39.333 --> 16:44.749
I've lived in this house
for 50 years.

16:44.750 --> 16:47.874
It's where I raised your father

16:47.875 --> 16:53.082
and where your grandfather
spent his last days.

16:53.083 --> 16:55.708
I'm just not ready to leave yet.

16:55.709 --> 16:57.666
Okay.

16:57.667 --> 17:01.874
I'll... we ll get everybody,
and we ll go back to the office.

17:01.875 --> 17:06.624
Okay, sweetheart,
and I'm sorry again, you know?

17:06.625 --> 17:09.499
I really don't mean
to be a bother.

17:09.500 --> 17:12.790
No, Grandma, you're n...
you're not a bother.

17:12.791 --> 17:14.915
Hey, I love you.

17:14.916 --> 17:18.457
I love you too.

17:18.458 --> 17:20.375
Let's go.

17:23.541 --> 17:26.540
(SOFT MUSIC)

17:26.541 --> 17:31.457
♪

17:31.458 --> 17:33.375
Bye.

17:41.291 --> 17:42.791
That's it?

17:42.792 --> 17:44.040
Only two moves scheduled today?

17:44.041 --> 17:45.833
Yup, we like to leave
enough time

17:45.834 --> 17:47.124
in between clients, you know?

17:47.125 --> 17:49.499
Also, not a lot of moves
coming in lately.

17:49.500 --> 17:52.499
See you at the party tonight.

17:52.500 --> 17:54.791
Hey.

17:54.792 --> 17:56.499
Thank you so much
for helping out today.

17:56.500 --> 17:58.833
I don't know,
I can barely lift my arms.

17:58.834 --> 17:59.834
They're so sore.

17:59.835 --> 18:01.666
Well, that is
because you insisted

18:01.667 --> 18:05.374
on lifting an entire loveseat
by yourself, so...

18:05.375 --> 18:07.833
I don't really
like to ask for help.

18:07.834 --> 18:10.833
Yeah.
I'm starting to get that.

18:10.834 --> 18:13.833
So now what we usually do is we
go through the day's checklist

18:13.834 --> 18:15.833
just to make sure
everything went smoothly.

18:15.834 --> 18:18.290
You know,
we also track inventory.

18:18.291 --> 18:21.208
(SNORING)

18:25.667 --> 18:28.708
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

18:28.709 --> 18:31.708
(MELLOW MUSIC)

18:31.709 --> 18:37.667
(MUSIC PLAYING)

18:39.375 --> 18:41.666
Oh, hello.
Can I have one of those?

18:41.667 --> 18:43.541
Yes, thank you so much.
That's very sweet.

18:43.542 --> 18:46.500
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

18:48.583 --> 18:51.040
Hi.
Look at those bags.

18:51.041 --> 18:53.374
Yeah, those are mine,
my... my idea.

18:53.375 --> 18:54.375
Good work.
Hi.

18:54.376 --> 18:57.833
So anyone... anyone of interest?
Hey.

18:57.834 --> 18:59.082
Uh, well, give it time.

18:59.083 --> 19:01.999
We just got here.
Wait, why? Do you see someone?

19:02.000 --> 19:05.082
Well, Midge is looking
quite elegant this evening.

19:05.083 --> 19:07.332
She's a couple decades
younger than my usual type,

19:07.333 --> 19:09.416
but Im... I'm feeling
a little adventurous.

19:09.417 --> 19:11.457
You know, if you want, I could
put in a good word for you.

19:11.458 --> 19:13.249
Yes, yes, please, please,
thank you.

19:13.250 --> 19:16.165
But seriously, we should set
each other up.

19:16.166 --> 19:19.708
Good idea, double date.
Done.

19:19.709 --> 19:22.249
Let's go say hi to Olivia.

19:22.250 --> 19:25.082
Let's go simple.
Just gonna have a beer.

19:25.083 --> 19:26.749
Okay.

19:26.750 --> 19:28.082
Great party.

19:28.083 --> 19:30.624
Mr. Fuller, glad
you could make it.

19:30.625 --> 19:32.624
I wouldn't miss it
for the world, Neil.

19:32.625 --> 19:34.374
Congratulations
on all your success.

19:34.375 --> 19:37.332
Thank you. It's, um... well,
it's just incredibly exciting.

19:37.333 --> 19:41.416
Uh, listen, um,
I was hoping we might be able

19:41.417 --> 19:42.749
to continue that conversation

19:42.750 --> 19:46.582
we started in my office.

19:46.583 --> 19:49.290
I didn't invite you here
for that.

19:49.291 --> 19:51.208
Will you excuse me?

19:54.333 --> 19:55.624
Olivia.

19:55.625 --> 19:59.624
Karen, oh, it's
so good to see you.

19:59.625 --> 20:01.874
I can't believe
you're actually here.

20:01.875 --> 20:03.666
Pete was just telling me...

20:03.667 --> 20:05.749
The Pie Shop?
Yeah.

20:05.750 --> 20:07.958
I love that you guys
still have that ritual.

20:07.959 --> 20:09.374
Well, I enjoy a good tradition.

20:09.375 --> 20:11.791
And I enjoy pie.
After all these years you guys

20:11.792 --> 20:13.082
are still such good friends,

20:13.083 --> 20:15.624
and I've lost touch
with most people.

20:15.625 --> 20:17.165
Well, actually,
it's not by choice.

20:17.166 --> 20:19.249
I can't get rid of him.

20:19.250 --> 20:21.124
Wow, I'm gonna pretend
I didn't hear that.

20:21.125 --> 20:23.791
There you are.

20:23.792 --> 20:26.791
Oh, you look just like
your mother,

20:26.792 --> 20:30.040
except you're far too serious.

20:30.041 --> 20:32.332
Hey, Midge.
Hi.

20:32.333 --> 20:35.916
We ll see you later.
Okay.

20:35.917 --> 20:38.834
So are you married?

20:45.917 --> 20:47.165
Hey, Dad.

20:47.166 --> 20:50.666
Hey, honey. How are you?

20:50.667 --> 20:52.249
What are you doing out here?

20:52.250 --> 20:55.374
Mm, just needed to think.
You?

20:55.375 --> 20:57.249
I was being interrogated.

20:57.250 --> 20:59.749
Midge?
Mm, who else?

20:59.750 --> 21:02.833
Well, she's harmless.
I don't know.

21:02.834 --> 21:04.749
She pinched
my cheeks pretty hard.

21:04.750 --> 21:09.165
That's Midge.

21:09.166 --> 21:10.499
Anything you want
to get off your chest?

21:10.500 --> 21:13.458
I don't think so.
(CHUCKLES)

21:15.542 --> 21:18.416
Anything you want
to get off yours?

21:18.417 --> 21:21.124
Yes, actually, yeah.

21:21.125 --> 21:25.791
I, uh... I wasn't being completely
honest before about the company.

21:25.792 --> 21:28.207
It's not doing so well.

21:28.208 --> 21:30.040
In fact,
there's a guy here tonight,

21:30.041 --> 21:33.499
Robert Fuller from
Acme Conglomerated.

21:33.500 --> 21:35.374
Yeah, I just met him.

21:35.375 --> 21:37.708
Well, he's chomping at the bit
to buy us out.

21:37.709 --> 21:39.833
Well, are you gonna sell?
No, no, I can't.

21:39.834 --> 21:42.541
No, your... your mother and I,
we built this company together.

21:42.542 --> 21:46.165
I-I mean, going into
the office every day,

21:46.166 --> 21:48.124
helping with the moves,

21:48.125 --> 21:49.874
it's what keeps her
memory alive.

21:49.875 --> 21:51.958
I just can't throw that away.

21:51.959 --> 21:55.332
Is that why you haven't
changed the answering machine?

21:55.333 --> 21:57.749
Yeah.

21:57.750 --> 21:59.541
I didn't have the heart
to delete it.

21:59.542 --> 22:01.374
I don't know, it's just...
it's just... it's all hitting

22:01.375 --> 22:02.958
at a bad time
with my trip and all.

22:02.959 --> 22:07.165
Dad, I could help.
What do you mean?

22:07.166 --> 22:10.207
Well, I can get the business
back on its feet.

22:10.208 --> 22:12.874
No, I'm not having you,
on your vacation, work.

22:12.875 --> 22:14.249
That... no. Thank you though.

22:14.250 --> 22:17.249
Dad, come on. I want to.

22:17.250 --> 22:20.624
Are you sure?

22:20.625 --> 22:25.374
Oh, sweetie,
I really appreciate this.

22:25.375 --> 22:26.833
Come on.

22:26.834 --> 22:29.666
Let's get back to the party.
Hey, gather around, you guys.

22:29.667 --> 22:33.499
Don't be shy.

22:33.500 --> 22:36.416
We are here to celebrate
25 years

22:36.417 --> 22:37.999
of the Wilson family
moving things,

22:38.000 --> 22:39.290
so I figure it was only
a matter of time

22:39.291 --> 22:41.374
that we should have Neil come up
and give us a few words.

22:41.375 --> 22:43.040
Come on, Neil.
Don't be shy.

22:43.041 --> 22:45.959
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

22:47.625 --> 22:50.290
Look, I am not one
to make speeches.

22:50.291 --> 22:52.541
Craig, you know this.

22:52.542 --> 22:54.708
Okay, but first of all,

22:54.709 --> 22:57.124
I just appreciate
that you're all here with us

22:57.125 --> 22:58.416
to celebrate this big day.

22:58.417 --> 23:00.708
My beautiful Debbie and I
started this company

23:00.709 --> 23:02.249
25 years ago,

23:02.250 --> 23:07.624
and we could not have done it
without your unwavering support.

23:07.625 --> 23:11.290
You are all truly
like family to me.

23:11.291 --> 23:13.249
All of us at Wilson Movers,

23:13.250 --> 23:14.624
well, we have gotten to witness

23:14.625 --> 23:16.374
first... well,

23:16.375 --> 23:19.916
first apartments, first houses,
new business ventures.

23:19.917 --> 23:22.124
And we always say
that every move was

23:22.125 --> 23:25.082
and is a new beginning,
a new possibility,

23:25.083 --> 23:27.332
and it is truly an honor

23:27.333 --> 23:29.332
to have been able
to be a part of that,

23:29.333 --> 23:31.999
and speaking of what matters
most, my beautiful,

23:32.000 --> 23:34.833
if I must say,
daughter Olivia is here.

23:34.834 --> 23:37.457
She's visiting from the Big Apple.

23:37.458 --> 23:38.874
She ll be here for a while,

23:38.875 --> 23:41.165
and I just want her
to say hello to everybody.

23:41.166 --> 23:44.207
Give a big wave, sweetie.
Isn't she beautiful?

23:44.208 --> 23:46.207
Okay, anyway,
thank you, everybody.

23:46.208 --> 23:48.416
Thank you for coming out
to celebrate with us,

23:48.417 --> 23:51.165
and what we say now
is let's enjoy this party!

23:51.166 --> 23:53.083
(APPLAUSE)
Yes.

23:58.500 --> 24:01.040
Most people clean up
after the party is over.

24:01.041 --> 24:03.708
Here. Let me help.

24:03.709 --> 24:06.416
Thanks.

24:06.417 --> 24:10.124
So what brought you
to Sierra Verde?

24:10.125 --> 24:13.124
Uh, my grandma, actually.

24:13.125 --> 24:16.374
I want to look out for her, so I
moved in with her for a while.

24:16.375 --> 24:19.833
Initially, the plan was
to save up money for law school,

24:19.834 --> 24:21.416
but things happen, you know?

24:21.417 --> 24:23.874
Is that still the plan,
to become a lawyer?

24:23.875 --> 24:25.958
I don't know. We ll see.

24:25.959 --> 24:28.541
What about you?
Interior design is your passion?

24:28.542 --> 24:32.374
Absolutely. I love it.
That's awesome.

24:32.375 --> 24:33.999
I hope that you can
bring this enthusiasm

24:34.000 --> 24:35.416
to the office, you know?

24:35.417 --> 24:37.582
Neil told me that you and I
are gonna be working together.

24:37.583 --> 24:39.207
I'll try not to step
on your toes.

24:39.208 --> 24:40.499
You don't need to worry
about anything.

24:40.500 --> 24:42.416
I'm a mover, so I'm used
to getting stepped on.

24:42.417 --> 24:45.916
Oh, I see.
Quite the fiesta.

24:45.917 --> 24:48.582
Oh, hey you.
Hey, I'm so sorry I'm late.

24:48.583 --> 24:50.416
Book club got a little
heated tonight.

24:50.417 --> 24:52.916
Oh.
Hi. I'm Heather.

24:52.917 --> 24:56.416
Olivia.
Oh, this is Neil's daughter.

24:56.417 --> 24:57.582
Oh.
Yeah.

24:57.583 --> 24:59.416
Oh, okay.
It's so nice to meet you.

24:59.417 --> 25:00.666
You too.

25:00.667 --> 25:02.583
Oh.

25:04.667 --> 25:07.958
Do you think
Neil's gonna retire soon?

25:07.959 --> 25:09.290
I don't know.

25:09.291 --> 25:13.207
No better person to take
over the company than you.

25:13.208 --> 25:17.249
Well, I mean, let's not jump
the gun here, okay?

25:17.250 --> 25:19.374
Pete has a real passion for it.

25:19.375 --> 25:22.207
Yeah, but you're great
with all the legal stuff.

25:22.208 --> 25:23.958
Neil loves you for that.

25:23.959 --> 25:25.999
Plus, he didn't put Pete
in charge while he was gone.

25:26.000 --> 25:27.499
He put you.

25:27.500 --> 25:29.916
I'm not even sure this is what
I want to be doing long-term.

25:29.917 --> 25:31.999
Well, you're not
gonna be doing this.

25:32.000 --> 25:34.416
You're gonna be
a business owner,

25:34.417 --> 25:36.040
and then we can start
living our lives.

25:36.041 --> 25:37.958
I thought we were
living our lives.

25:37.959 --> 25:40.958
No, you know what I mean,
take the next step.

25:40.959 --> 25:43.958
(SOFT MUSIC)

25:43.959 --> 25:50.332
(MUSIC PLAYING)

25:50.333 --> 25:52.833
Yeah, sorry to call so late.
I know you're three hours ahead.

25:52.834 --> 25:54.374
Lucky for you I'm a night owl.

25:54.375 --> 25:56.582
So how was the party?

25:56.583 --> 25:58.499
Did you meet any guys?

25:58.500 --> 26:02.124
Ugh, definitely not.
That's a bummer.

26:02.125 --> 26:04.708
No, it's fine.

26:04.709 --> 26:07.332
Well, in other news,
my dad's leaving me

26:07.333 --> 26:08.833
in charge of the company
while he goes away.

26:08.834 --> 26:12.791
That's kind of a big deal,
doing that all by yourself.

26:12.792 --> 26:16.165
Not entirely by myself.

26:16.166 --> 26:18.416
(SOFT MUSIC)

26:18.417 --> 26:21.791
Okay. Hey, thanks for coming
in early today, guys.

26:21.792 --> 26:23.416
I really appreciate it.

26:23.417 --> 26:25.165
I have got to leave for my trip
in a few minutes here.

26:25.166 --> 26:29.749
So as a thank-you,
breakfast burritos on the house.

26:29.750 --> 26:33.749
Mr. Craig, Scott,
and no-peppers Pete.

26:33.750 --> 26:35.666
Now, this is a professional,
gentlemen. Take note.

26:35.667 --> 26:37.082
Thanks, Dad.
How are you?

26:37.083 --> 26:39.332
So that's really what
you're gonna be wearing?

26:39.333 --> 26:41.332
I thought you learned
that moving's a dirty job.

26:41.333 --> 26:43.082
Yeah, I did, but, you know,

26:43.083 --> 26:44.708
I just figured
I'd stick around here today.

26:44.709 --> 26:46.374
I like it.
That's a great idea.

26:46.375 --> 26:47.666
Okay, Olivia will be in charge

26:47.667 --> 26:49.165
of the office, paperwork,
etcetera.

26:49.166 --> 26:52.708
Scott, you ll be in charge
of the moves. Sound good?

26:52.709 --> 26:55.124
That sounds good.
We got work to do.

26:55.125 --> 26:56.833
Oh, before I forget,
the accountant is gonna be here

26:56.834 --> 26:58.749
in the next couple of weeks
to work on the taxes,

26:58.750 --> 27:01.791
and I can't find the file
with last year's receipts.

27:01.792 --> 27:03.749
Could you please take a look?
It's a lot of papers,

27:03.750 --> 27:05.374
but I promise
they're in there somewhere.

27:05.375 --> 27:08.040
Yes, I'll handle it.
Thanks, sweetie.

27:08.041 --> 27:10.040
You're gonna do great.
I'm really excited about this.

27:10.041 --> 27:12.541
Have fun on your trip.
I promise.

27:12.542 --> 27:14.249
Oh, thank you for doing this.
I love you.

27:14.250 --> 27:16.208
I love you too.

27:20.917 --> 27:23.374
He doesn't want to sell, Dave.

27:23.375 --> 27:24.624
He won't budge.

27:24.625 --> 27:27.666
Relax, Rob.
You're still establishing roots.

27:27.667 --> 27:30.332
I'm only supposed to be here
to set up shop.

27:30.333 --> 27:34.332
I can't move on until we've
absolved all our competition.

27:34.333 --> 27:37.416
All right, okay. I think
I got a connection who can help.

27:37.417 --> 27:38.791
I'll be in touch.

27:38.792 --> 27:41.499
Wilson Family Movers
is going down.

27:41.500 --> 27:43.833
They might as well go ahead
and start packing their bags.

27:43.834 --> 27:45.750
True story, baby.

27:50.333 --> 27:52.791
Where's Craig and Pete?

27:52.792 --> 27:55.958
All the moves were
canceled today, so...

27:55.959 --> 27:58.457
Oh. Does that happen a lot?

27:58.458 --> 28:01.541
More and more now
that Acme's prices are lower.

28:01.542 --> 28:03.249
So what do we do now?

28:03.250 --> 28:05.708
There is nothing much to do.

28:05.709 --> 28:08.165
Should we check the inventory?
Done.

28:08.166 --> 28:10.207
Wash the trucks?
They are so clean you could

28:10.208 --> 28:12.040
eat off of them,
and I filled up the tanks too.

28:12.041 --> 28:16.332
Why don't you take a seat,
relax, put your feet up?

28:16.333 --> 28:19.958
No. Um, I think I'm gonna
start reorganizing the office.

28:19.959 --> 28:21.917
Okay.

28:24.875 --> 28:27.874
(SOFT MUSIC)

28:27.875 --> 28:34.792
(MUSIC PLAYING)

28:42.417 --> 28:45.249
It's, uh, organized chaos
in here, huh?

28:45.250 --> 28:47.249
That is not organized chaos.

28:47.250 --> 28:49.791
That is just chaos-chaos.

28:49.792 --> 28:51.499
All right, well,
if you need me, I'm right here.

28:51.500 --> 28:56.499
Thanks, but, you know, I do
my best work when I'm alone.

28:56.500 --> 28:57.749
You know what?

28:57.750 --> 28:59.040
Why don't you just take
the rest of the day off?

28:59.041 --> 29:00.499
Mm, I don't know about that.

29:00.500 --> 29:03.999
Neil asked me to watch over the
moves and to look out for you.

29:04.000 --> 29:07.791
Oh, I'm fine. As you said,
there aren't any moves today.

29:07.792 --> 29:10.999
I got this, okay?
See you tomorrow?

29:11.000 --> 29:13.999
Okay.
Great.

29:14.000 --> 29:16.999
Don't work too hard, now.

29:17.000 --> 29:19.499
I never understood
that expression.

29:19.500 --> 29:21.833
If one's gonna work,
might as well work hard.

29:21.834 --> 29:24.666
What's wrong with working
hard, anyway?

29:24.667 --> 29:26.583
Nothing.

29:30.542 --> 29:32.833
Okay, so I have
this new girl from work.

29:32.834 --> 29:34.874
Her name is Lily.
She's really pretty,

29:34.875 --> 29:37.207
and she has tons
of interests and hobbies.

29:37.208 --> 29:39.749
Will she laugh at my jokes?
Well, that's to be determined.

29:39.750 --> 29:40.791
Okay.

29:40.792 --> 29:43.290
All right, so who do
you have for me?

29:43.291 --> 29:45.457
I met this guy, Andrew,
the other day at yoga class,

29:45.458 --> 29:46.791
seems cool.

29:46.792 --> 29:48.249
He's really spiritual, and, um...

29:48.250 --> 29:49.874
But is he a good person?

29:49.875 --> 29:53.207
I just want someone who's gonna
respect me and care about me.

29:53.208 --> 29:54.958
Look, there's no way that
any guy in his right mind

29:54.959 --> 29:57.040
would not care about you.
You're amazing.

29:57.041 --> 29:59.959
Okay, you can have a bite.

30:02.917 --> 30:05.165
Mmm, that is good.

30:05.166 --> 30:08.165
(UPBEAT ROCK MUSIC)

30:08.166 --> 30:15.125
(MUSIC PLAYING)

30:34.750 --> 30:38.165
Yeah, no, I'm glad
that you're free from work.

30:38.166 --> 30:40.499
It's... it's a treat.
We don't get to do this.

30:40.500 --> 30:42.040
Yeah, there's not much

30:42.041 --> 30:44.249
going on at the office
right now, so...

30:44.250 --> 30:46.666
How are things
with Neil's daughter?

30:46.667 --> 30:48.374
Is she trying to take charge
over there?

30:48.375 --> 30:52.249
She's just there temporarily.
She's an interior designer.

30:52.250 --> 30:56.541
Have you ever thought
about working at Acme?

30:56.542 --> 30:58.624
I saw an ad that they're hiring,

30:58.625 --> 31:00.124
and they're looking
for more employees.

31:00.125 --> 31:01.624
That would be
such a good job for you.

31:01.625 --> 31:03.290
It would be such a step up.

31:03.291 --> 31:05.290
That's Wilson's
biggest competitor.

31:05.291 --> 31:08.165
Hey, I know that you have goals,

31:08.166 --> 31:10.249
I do, but we both know

31:10.250 --> 31:14.791
that you're just not the best
at following through with them.

31:14.792 --> 31:17.416
I'm just trying to help.

31:17.417 --> 31:20.333
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

31:21.083 --> 31:24.082
(MELLOW MUSIC)

31:24.083 --> 31:31.000
(MUSIC PLAYING)

31:47.500 --> 31:50.791
(LAUGHING)

31:50.792 --> 31:52.499
Are you ready
for our moonlight stroll?

31:52.500 --> 31:56.332
Oh, I sure am.
Okay.

31:56.333 --> 31:58.416
You know,
I just can't help thinking,

31:58.417 --> 31:59.833
how is Olivia doing at work?

31:59.834 --> 32:03.332
Why don't you give her a call?
Eh, no.

32:03.333 --> 32:05.999
I mean, I want her to know
that I have faith in her, so...

32:06.000 --> 32:08.416
anyways, she can call me
if she needs to.

32:08.417 --> 32:09.958
I'm sure everything's
going great,

32:09.959 --> 32:11.499
and from what
you've told me about,

32:11.500 --> 32:12.833
I think she can carry her own.

32:12.834 --> 32:15.541
Well, she is a hard worker,
always has been.

32:15.542 --> 32:16.999
I can't wait to meet her.

32:17.000 --> 32:18.874
Yeah, one day.

32:18.875 --> 32:20.874
When do you think
that's gonna be?

32:20.875 --> 32:22.165
Uh, you know, I don't know.

32:22.166 --> 32:24.708
She's... she's sensitive.

32:24.709 --> 32:28.708
I'm beginning to think you're
using her as an excuse.

32:28.709 --> 32:30.958
That's not true.

32:30.959 --> 32:32.416
I overheard her phone call.

32:32.417 --> 32:34.833
She lost her job.
Oh, no.

32:34.834 --> 32:37.165
And I'm just trying
to be extra careful.

32:37.166 --> 32:39.916
Okay. I understand.
Thank you.

32:39.917 --> 32:41.541
And I'm sorry.
Oh, thank you.

32:41.542 --> 32:44.416
We will find the perfect time,
I promise.

32:44.417 --> 32:48.165
Good.
What's over here?

32:48.166 --> 32:51.165
(LIGHT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

32:51.166 --> 32:57.916
(MUSIC PLAYING)

32:57.917 --> 33:00.875
(SIGHS)

33:02.417 --> 33:05.582
Hi.

33:05.583 --> 33:08.290
(SNIFFS)

33:08.291 --> 33:10.666
What's that smell?
Clean.

33:10.667 --> 33:13.040
No.
I'm kidding.

33:13.041 --> 33:16.165
Light floral notes
have a soothing effect.

33:16.166 --> 33:18.874
Cool. Nice work.

33:18.875 --> 33:22.416
Whoa, Olivia,
the place looks great.

33:22.417 --> 33:24.833
Yeah, I'm impressed.
It's like one of those

33:24.834 --> 33:27.165
staged offices at IKEA,
you know what I mean?

33:27.166 --> 33:29.457
You've seen it before?
Yeah.

33:29.458 --> 33:32.666
Like, it's textbook?

33:32.667 --> 33:36.249
This could definitely be
in a textbook.

33:36.250 --> 33:39.499
What happened to my desk?

33:39.500 --> 33:40.958
What do you think?

33:40.959 --> 33:43.874
I tried to buy some new chairs,
but I'll have to order them.

33:43.875 --> 33:47.541
Where's my rubber band ball?

33:47.542 --> 33:49.457
Do you know how long it took me
to make that?

33:49.458 --> 33:51.666
Well, surprisingly, it didn't
take that long to pull apart.

33:51.667 --> 33:52.833
You know, your Dad asked you
to help,

33:52.834 --> 33:54.624
not rearrange our office space.

33:54.625 --> 33:55.749
Hey, where's last week's paper?

33:55.750 --> 33:57.165
I always do the puzzle
on the back.

33:57.166 --> 33:59.457
I threw it out. It's easy
for newspapers to pile up,

33:59.458 --> 34:00.958
and just...
things get out of hand.

34:00.959 --> 34:01.959
I've been doing that puzzle
every week

34:01.960 --> 34:03.416
for the last 40 years.

34:03.417 --> 34:04.624
I mean, you can't just go
through people's personal

34:04.625 --> 34:06.040
belongings
and trash them, Olivia.

34:06.041 --> 34:07.791
Where's my signed
baseball collection?

34:07.792 --> 34:10.498
It was making your desk
look small and cluttered,

34:10.500 --> 34:12.248
and it's not
a good work environment,

34:12.250 --> 34:15.123
so I just put them
in that box under your desk.

34:15.125 --> 34:16.125
Look, why don't you talk to us

34:16.126 --> 34:17.833
before you started
making these changes?

34:17.833 --> 34:20.291
I'm sorry.
I was just trying to help.

34:27.291 --> 34:29.208
My baseballs, man.

34:36.500 --> 34:39.498
(SOFT MUSIC)

34:39.500 --> 34:46.458
(MUSIC PLAYING)

34:47.667 --> 34:49.666
(GRUNTS)

34:49.667 --> 34:56.583
(MUSIC PLAYING)

35:00.166 --> 35:02.708
I was just trying
to do something nice.

35:02.709 --> 35:03.999
Don't you think it's
a little intrusive

35:04.000 --> 35:06.416
to go through somebody's
desk without asking?

35:06.417 --> 35:08.374
No, I was just trying
to get things organized.

35:08.375 --> 35:11.749
Yeah, but none of us
could find anything.

35:11.750 --> 35:13.290
(SIGHS)

35:13.291 --> 35:15.374
I guess I should have listened
to the client.

35:15.375 --> 35:18.291
Huh?
Never mind.

35:19.834 --> 35:21.582
So do you always hide
in moving trucks?

35:21.583 --> 35:23.165
(CHUCKLES)

35:23.166 --> 35:25.083
I used to.

35:26.834 --> 35:29.541
When I was eight years
old I stormed out of my room,

35:29.542 --> 35:31.457
and I said I was
running away forever,

35:31.458 --> 35:33.541
and I ended up just camping out

35:33.542 --> 35:35.124
in Annabel
for a couple of hours,

35:35.125 --> 35:38.374
and then I went crawling back
into my Mom's arms.

35:38.375 --> 35:41.666
This truck has a name?
They all do.

35:41.667 --> 35:43.207
Annabel is my favorite though.

35:43.208 --> 35:47.207
There's Dillard, Susie Q, Kitty.

35:47.208 --> 35:49.249
Kitty? Why... why is it Kitty?

35:49.250 --> 35:51.374
Because when I was
little I wanted a pet,

35:51.375 --> 35:53.332
but my Dad said
I could have a truck instead.

35:53.333 --> 35:56.250
Ah, okay.
I like his style.

35:59.041 --> 36:02.916
Hey, uh, so you ready
to get back in there?

36:02.917 --> 36:04.749
I don't know.

36:04.750 --> 36:06.958
But you made Neil's office
all organized

36:06.959 --> 36:10.916
and smell like... what was it,
light floral notes?

36:10.917 --> 36:12.749
I don't know.

36:12.750 --> 36:16.874
It was inauthentic and textbook

36:16.875 --> 36:20.082
and cold and sterile,

36:20.083 --> 36:22.582
and that's exactly my problem,

36:22.583 --> 36:25.500
and that's why I lost my job.

36:27.583 --> 36:30.124
Please don't say anything.

36:30.125 --> 36:31.541
I haven't told anyone.

36:31.542 --> 36:33.458
No, I won't.

36:38.542 --> 36:41.541
(JAZZY MUSIC)

36:41.542 --> 36:47.332
(MUSIC PLAYING)

36:47.333 --> 36:49.833
Good evening, sir.

36:49.834 --> 36:52.207
Thanks.

36:52.208 --> 36:53.416
Hey.
Hey.

36:53.417 --> 36:54.833
So are they here yet?

36:54.834 --> 36:57.958
No, no, not yet.

36:57.959 --> 37:00.958
I'm not gonna lie,
I don't know about this, man.

37:00.959 --> 37:02.916
You're gonna love her.
(SIGHS)

37:02.917 --> 37:06.834
Come on.
All right, let's do this.

37:08.959 --> 37:10.582
I can't believe you
talked me into this.

37:10.583 --> 37:11.916
I don't get set up.

37:11.917 --> 37:13.499
I like things
to happen organically.

37:13.500 --> 37:15.791
Besides, if he's so great,
why aren't you dating him?

37:15.792 --> 37:17.541
Pete and I are just friends.

37:17.542 --> 37:19.708
Okay, when a guy and
a girl are just friends,

37:19.709 --> 37:21.999
usually one of them
isn't attracted to the other.

37:22.000 --> 37:25.332
You're gorgeous,
so he must be...

37:25.333 --> 37:26.624
displeasing to the eye?

37:26.625 --> 37:29.332
Oh, no, he's so cute.

37:29.333 --> 37:31.874
We've just known each other for
so long, since we were little.

37:31.875 --> 37:33.666
So it's like
a brother-sister thing?

37:33.667 --> 37:35.708
I mean, kind of?

37:35.709 --> 37:37.165
Just come.

37:37.166 --> 37:38.374
We ll have a great time.

37:38.375 --> 37:39.749
It ll be fine, okay?

37:39.750 --> 37:46.457
For me, and trust me,
Pete is... he's the greatest.

37:46.458 --> 37:49.582
Okay.
I don't know about this.

37:49.583 --> 37:52.582
(LIGHT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

37:52.583 --> 37:55.708
(MUSIC PLAYING)

37:55.709 --> 37:57.040
So you found parking okay?

37:57.041 --> 37:58.999
Thanks.

37:59.000 --> 38:00.666
Yeah, two blocks away for me.

38:00.667 --> 38:03.040
This guy he doesn't... he
doesn't care if he walks a mile.

38:03.041 --> 38:04.708
He's so cheap.
He doesn't... you know.

38:04.709 --> 38:05.916
Thanks, Andrew.

38:05.917 --> 38:08.958
So you've lived here
your whole life?

38:08.959 --> 38:11.082
Yeah, yeah, born
and raised, yeah. You?

38:11.083 --> 38:12.541
I moved here when I was eight.

38:12.542 --> 38:17.124
Oh, cool, cool.
Yeah.

38:17.125 --> 38:20.290
Um, all right, so, uh,
what are we ordering?

38:20.291 --> 38:22.416
I heard the burgers are great.

38:22.417 --> 38:24.708
BOTH: I'm vegan.

38:24.709 --> 38:26.541
You are?
Yeah.

38:26.542 --> 38:28.791
It's so rare to find
other people who are...

38:28.792 --> 38:30.374
I know, right?
Oh, this menu.

38:30.375 --> 38:31.708
Tell me about it.

38:31.709 --> 38:35.374
I mean, it is, like, totally not
vegan-friendly at all.

38:35.375 --> 38:38.374
I'm sorry. Pete should have
picked a different place.

38:38.375 --> 38:39.499
I-I forgot.

38:39.500 --> 38:41.708
So how long have
you been vegan for?

38:41.709 --> 38:42.791
About five years now.

38:42.792 --> 38:44.457
What made you decide to do that?

38:44.458 --> 38:46.417
On a trip to Montana

38:51.250 --> 38:54.666
(PHONE RINGING)

38:54.667 --> 38:56.791
Hey, P.
Hey, what's up?

38:56.792 --> 38:59.457
Just at work.
Still?

38:59.458 --> 39:01.040
Yeah. You?

39:01.041 --> 39:02.958
Just hanging out
with some friends from school.

39:02.959 --> 39:05.874
So how's everything been going?
(SIGHS)

39:05.875 --> 39:09.874
Well, I accidentally told Scott
I was fired, so there's that.

39:09.875 --> 39:12.124
What did he say?
It doesn't matter.

39:12.125 --> 39:15.165
I shouldn't even have told him.
I haven't even told my Dad.

39:15.166 --> 39:17.541
Definitely not
the end of the world.

39:17.542 --> 39:18.791
Everything will be cool.

39:18.792 --> 39:19.792
Yeah, you're right.

39:19.793 --> 39:21.749
So is anyone else
there with you?

39:21.750 --> 39:24.666
No. I'm the only one
without a social life.

39:24.667 --> 39:26.874
Okay, you should definitely
get one of those.

39:26.875 --> 39:29.040
Nah, I'm okay.

39:29.041 --> 39:31.416
Well, I got to get back to work.
Talk tomorrow?

39:31.417 --> 39:34.333
Yup, bye.
Okay, bye.

39:38.709 --> 39:41.791
Okay, so what do you think?
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

39:41.792 --> 39:46.249
Pete? Yeah, he's nice.

39:46.250 --> 39:48.833
How about you and Andrew?

39:48.834 --> 39:52.416
I don't know. He seems
a little New Age-y for me,

39:52.417 --> 39:55.165
but maybe if I hang out
with him again.

39:55.166 --> 39:57.374
So you think you two
will go out again?

39:57.375 --> 40:00.374
I don't know.
Because I kind of like him.

40:00.375 --> 40:02.332
Yeah, I did see that.
You know, it's... it's

40:02.333 --> 40:04.666
so rare to find someone
who likes heavy metal

40:04.667 --> 40:06.749
and practices meditation.

40:06.750 --> 40:09.499
It is a weird combination.
I can't believe Lily

40:09.500 --> 40:10.916
has those same interests.

40:10.917 --> 40:14.207
Wait, so are you not...
not into... into Karen?

40:14.208 --> 40:15.958
Who?

40:15.959 --> 40:18.999
Oh, this is, uh... this is me
right here. You want a ride?

40:19.000 --> 40:21.666
Yeah, sure. Thank you.
Great.

40:21.667 --> 40:23.833
Um, nice meeting you, Pete.

40:23.834 --> 40:25.124
Karen, see you at work?

40:25.125 --> 40:27.666
Yeah.
Yeah, nice...

40:27.667 --> 40:29.625
nice meeting you too.

40:33.792 --> 40:35.082
Well, I guess it's time

40:35.083 --> 40:37.582
to reactivate
my dating online profile.

40:37.583 --> 40:40.542
Yeah, me too. Let's go.

40:45.667 --> 40:48.374
Robarino,
it's Christmastime, buddy.

40:48.375 --> 40:50.207
What do you have?

40:50.208 --> 40:53.749
I got a competitive advantage
that ll seal the deal.

40:53.750 --> 40:55.666
I'm listening.
Just sent you an email,

40:55.667 --> 40:57.624
has the closing dates
of every home

40:57.625 --> 40:59.207
and business in Sierra Verde.

40:59.208 --> 41:01.999
You see, when homes
close people move in,

41:02.000 --> 41:04.374
and people move out,
and they hire movers for that.

41:04.375 --> 41:06.249
And I think they'd be
more inclined to hire

41:06.250 --> 41:09.207
Acme if you already call them.

41:09.208 --> 41:10.958
I'm good with that.

41:10.959 --> 41:12.874
Nothing like
a little healthy competition.

41:12.875 --> 41:14.875
My thoughts exactly.

41:18.542 --> 41:22.499
(QUIRKY MUSIC)

41:22.500 --> 41:24.666
(SNAPPING)

41:24.667 --> 41:31.583
(MUSIC PLAYING)

41:41.667 --> 41:48.583
(MUSIC PLAYING)

41:52.583 --> 41:55.499
(PHONE RINGING)

41:55.500 --> 41:56.708
(PHONE BEEPS)

41:56.709 --> 41:59.708
Wilson Family Movers,
Olivia speaking.

41:59.709 --> 42:02.749
Wh... yeah.

42:02.750 --> 42:06.499
Okay, um, is there
anything we could do?

42:06.500 --> 42:08.416
One last question, um,

42:08.417 --> 42:12.124
what company will be moving you?

42:12.125 --> 42:14.249
Acme.

42:14.250 --> 42:16.541
Right, the discount.

42:16.542 --> 42:17.833
Okay.

42:17.834 --> 42:20.916
Thank you so much. Bye.

42:20.917 --> 42:22.834
(PHONE BEEPS)

42:29.625 --> 42:32.207
Not... not exactly
what was in the plan.

42:32.208 --> 42:34.165
It's so peaceful out here.
Yeah.

42:34.166 --> 42:35.833
(PHONE RINGING)
Oh, you spoke too soon.

42:35.834 --> 42:37.457
Oh, come on.
Okay, that is on you.

42:37.458 --> 42:38.749
Never say that out loud.

42:38.750 --> 42:40.916
That is not my fault.
Never say... it's Olivia.

42:40.917 --> 42:43.124
Let me grab this.
Okay.

42:43.125 --> 42:45.416
(PHONE BEEPS)
Hey, honey, what's up?

42:45.417 --> 42:47.290
Hey, Dad.
Is this a good time?

42:47.291 --> 42:50.207
Yeah, yeah, yeah, I'm just,
um... I'm taking a hike.

42:50.208 --> 42:52.416
We had three
cancellations today.

42:52.417 --> 42:53.457
Really?

42:53.458 --> 42:54.999
It's Acme's discount.

42:55.000 --> 42:56.833
You know,
I just don't understand it.

42:56.834 --> 42:59.082
Our company,
we offer personality and heart,

42:59.083 --> 43:01.332
and Acme walks in,

43:01.333 --> 43:02.791
and all they have
are lower prices.

43:02.792 --> 43:03.999
Sorry, I shouldn't have called.

43:04.000 --> 43:05.332
I don't mean to disturb you.

43:05.333 --> 43:06.999
No, you're not.
No, I'm... no.

43:07.000 --> 43:09.332
Of course I'm glad you called,
any time.

43:09.333 --> 43:12.874
I just feel bad
I'm not there to help out.

43:12.875 --> 43:14.624
I'm not embarrassed to tell you,
honey, I'm kind of stumped.

43:14.625 --> 43:15.833
I don't know what to do.

43:15.834 --> 43:20.040
I will take any suggestions
you have.

43:20.041 --> 43:22.749
Don't worry, I know what to do.

43:22.750 --> 43:25.332
Okay, thanks, sweetie.
I'll see you soon.

43:25.333 --> 43:28.749
Bye-bye.

43:28.750 --> 43:31.708
Everything all right?
Yeah, yeah, no, it's fine.

43:31.709 --> 43:34.416
Neil, come on, talk to me.

43:34.417 --> 43:36.374
The company's not doing so good.

43:36.375 --> 43:39.249
The company's been causing you
a lot of stress lately,

43:39.250 --> 43:42.749
and it's just... it's not healthy
to be so on edge.

43:42.750 --> 43:44.916
Ever since we met,
I have been thinking

43:44.917 --> 43:46.999
about starting
my next chapter of my life,

43:47.000 --> 43:49.040
you know,
leaving the company behind,

43:49.041 --> 43:50.874
going into early retirement.

43:50.875 --> 43:53.207
I think you know I would love
to spend more time with you.

43:53.208 --> 43:56.708
I know you love the company,
and it has lots of memories.

43:56.709 --> 44:00.165
The company is all I have left
of Debbie. That's it.

44:00.166 --> 44:02.708
Okay, wouldn't she want
what's best for you?

44:02.709 --> 44:04.625
Wouldn't she want you
to be happy?

44:09.458 --> 44:11.958
I've been doing some thinking.
We don't have any moves

44:11.959 --> 44:13.791
scheduled over
the next three days,

44:13.792 --> 44:17.207
so I think that we should
take this down time to improve,

44:17.208 --> 44:18.749
gain a competitive edge,

44:18.750 --> 44:21.916
and we as soldiers
need to be prepped for go time.

44:21.917 --> 44:25.582
Hold on, I think you're being
just a little bit too intense.

44:25.583 --> 44:26.999
No. Okay.

44:27.000 --> 44:29.416
If we can't compete on pricing,
Acme steals our clients.

44:29.417 --> 44:32.624
We have to be more efficient
and do more moves in less time.

44:32.625 --> 44:34.999
Pete, I need to meet with you
every day for at least two hours

44:35.000 --> 44:36.290
to go over
all the potential moves

44:36.291 --> 44:37.749
and make sure
they run efficiently.

44:37.750 --> 44:41.082
Oh, also, do we have
any online systems in place?

44:41.083 --> 44:42.749
Everything we have is
in paper form.

44:42.750 --> 44:45.874
That means
the filing systems are ancient.

44:45.875 --> 44:47.582
Our setup is nothing
compared to Acme's.

44:47.583 --> 44:49.416
I mean, they have a website

44:49.417 --> 44:51.374
with an easy-access
appointment system.

44:51.375 --> 44:53.416
You don't even have
to talk to actual people.

44:53.417 --> 44:55.249
I mean, all you do
is input the information,

44:55.250 --> 44:56.457
and the moves are set.

44:56.458 --> 44:58.165
Look, I know you guys
don't want to do this,

44:58.166 --> 44:59.582
but it's make it
or break it time

44:59.583 --> 45:01.040
for Wilson Family Movers.

45:01.041 --> 45:03.624
My Dad entrusted me
with these responsibilities

45:03.625 --> 45:07.082
while he was away.

45:07.083 --> 45:09.000
I want to help.

45:11.125 --> 45:13.124
Who's with me?

45:13.125 --> 45:16.124
(SWELLING MUSIC)

45:16.125 --> 45:17.958
(MUSIC PLAYING)

45:17.959 --> 45:21.124
(UPBEAT ROCK MUSIC)

45:21.125 --> 45:23.874
<i>♪ There's nothing left
to say ♪</i>

45:23.875 --> 45:25.749
ALL: Go!

45:25.750 --> 45:27.999
It's moving wars.

45:28.000 --> 45:29.541
Customer service,
being professional,

45:29.542 --> 45:30.916
and getting the job done
with a smile

45:30.917 --> 45:33.833
on your face is crucial.

45:33.834 --> 45:37.624
<i>♪ I can't waste
another day ♪</i>

45:37.625 --> 45:40.666
<i>♪ The check is off
there are bills to pay ♪</i>

45:40.667 --> 45:43.749
<i>♪ But everything
is gonna be all right ♪</i>

45:43.750 --> 45:48.457
You have to load things
without any scratches.

45:48.458 --> 45:50.332
Think ahead and be willing
to transport items

45:50.333 --> 45:54.541
that other carriers won't touch.

45:54.542 --> 45:56.708
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

45:56.709 --> 46:01.165
<i>♪ Gotta keep moving ♪</i>

46:01.166 --> 46:04.624
Listen, I'm gonna talk to her.

46:04.625 --> 46:08.499
Excuse me, Olivia?
How is this helping?

46:08.500 --> 46:10.499
I don't think you understand
the severity of the situation.

46:10.500 --> 46:12.207
This company could crumble
to the ground.

46:12.208 --> 46:14.708
I get that you're a hard
worker and you're passionate,

46:14.709 --> 46:16.165
and you know what?
That's great.

46:16.166 --> 46:19.249
I respect that, but you can't
just do whatever you want.

46:19.250 --> 46:21.582
What is that supposed to mean?
You know what it means?

46:21.583 --> 46:23.624
It means that you've been here
all of two minutes,

46:23.625 --> 46:26.207
and already you're rearranging
our office without input.

46:26.208 --> 46:28.082
You're putting us through
some kind of boot camp

46:28.083 --> 46:29.582
as if you know what's best
for the company.

46:29.583 --> 46:33.040
You don't know how things work.
You haven't been here.

46:33.041 --> 46:36.082
Well, at least
I'm being proactive.

46:36.083 --> 46:38.082
What?
Your LSATs?

46:38.083 --> 46:39.207
They're great, Scott.

46:39.208 --> 46:40.916
You're just too afraid
to send them in.

46:40.917 --> 46:42.541
How do you... how do you know
about my LSATs?

46:42.542 --> 46:43.833
You want to go to law school?

46:43.834 --> 46:46.541
Stop being so passive
and do something about it.

46:46.542 --> 46:50.082
Bossy and mean, now I know
why you got fired.

46:50.083 --> 46:52.834
(SOFT MUSIC)

46:53.959 --> 46:56.999
(MELLOW MUSIC)

46:57.000 --> 46:59.332
(MUSIC PLAYING)

46:59.333 --> 47:01.416
Pete.

47:01.417 --> 47:03.249
Hey.

47:03.250 --> 47:05.582
Rough day?
Yeah.

47:05.583 --> 47:07.207
Wow, you look nice.

47:07.208 --> 47:08.499
Thanks.

47:08.500 --> 47:10.708
So what's with all this?

47:10.709 --> 47:11.999
Olivia put us through
the wringer,

47:12.000 --> 47:14.582
something about moving wars.

47:14.583 --> 47:16.624
Yeah, she always was
a little bossy.

47:16.625 --> 47:19.082
I wish Neil could see me
in that leadership role.

47:19.083 --> 47:20.582
Yeah, you'd be great at it.

47:20.583 --> 47:22.833
Yeah, but it's not gonna
happen anytime soon.

47:22.834 --> 47:24.082
Yeah, but it will, Pete.

47:24.083 --> 47:27.457
You just have to keep your nose
to the grindstone.

47:27.458 --> 47:29.290
At least you like your job.

47:29.291 --> 47:32.290
I don't know how much longer
I can be a receptionist.

47:32.291 --> 47:35.457
Okay, so I say we eat this pie
and go watch a movie.

47:35.458 --> 47:36.916
I can't.
Why?

47:36.917 --> 47:42.249
Do you... you got some hot date
you didn't tell me about?

47:42.250 --> 47:43.416
Who's the guy?

47:43.417 --> 47:45.290
I met him online.
That's awesome.

47:45.291 --> 47:48.250
Yeah, and I have you
to thank for fixing my profile.

47:58.125 --> 48:01.582
(SIGHS)

48:01.583 --> 48:04.874
This place is so organized.

48:04.875 --> 48:07.290
Olivia's driving me up the wall.

48:07.291 --> 48:09.124
You are so worked up tonight.

48:09.125 --> 48:11.040
You know, she's a perfectionist?

48:11.041 --> 48:12.332
It's like she has this picture

48:12.333 --> 48:14.165
in her mind of how everything's
supposed to be,

48:14.166 --> 48:15.958
and it's not reality,

48:15.959 --> 48:17.708
but at the same time
it makes me feel

48:17.709 --> 48:19.916
like I haven't been doing
anything with my life,

48:19.917 --> 48:22.249
like all... like all I do
is move people's furniture.

48:22.250 --> 48:23.999
No, you make
an honest living, Scott.

48:24.000 --> 48:26.708
You help people move into
their homes with their families.

48:26.709 --> 48:27.958
That's amazing.

48:27.959 --> 48:30.332
Yeah, but that's not
what I want to do.

48:30.333 --> 48:33.040
What is it that you want to do?

48:33.041 --> 48:35.541
I'm applying to law school.

48:35.542 --> 48:38.708
Law school?

48:38.709 --> 48:40.582
Scott, we talked about this.

48:40.583 --> 48:43.457
We ll go deeper into debt,
and you might not even finish.

48:43.458 --> 48:45.708
I thought... I thought
you'd be happy for me.

48:45.709 --> 48:46.958
Why would you say that?

48:46.959 --> 48:48.332
Look, I didn't want
to tell you this before,

48:48.333 --> 48:49.999
but I-I called Acme,

48:50.000 --> 48:53.040
and Robert Fuller said that
he would love to talk to you.

48:53.041 --> 48:55.666
I can't believe you went
behind my back and did that.

48:55.667 --> 48:57.290
Well, I didn't know
I went behind your back.

48:57.291 --> 48:58.624
Yeah, but I've told you,
Heather.

48:58.625 --> 48:59.749
I've told you repeatedly

48:59.750 --> 49:02.582
I don't want to do this
for the rest of my life.

49:02.583 --> 49:05.165
Well, you... you want to go to
a big city and become a lawyer?

49:05.166 --> 49:06.374
That's not what I want.

49:06.375 --> 49:08.916
I know.

49:08.917 --> 49:11.916
(SOFT MUSIC)

49:11.917 --> 49:16.541
(MUSIC PLAYING)

49:16.542 --> 49:19.624
Well, then, I guess that...

49:19.625 --> 49:23.874
we don't want the same things.

49:23.875 --> 49:27.541
Yeah, it looks that way.

49:27.542 --> 49:29.374
I should go then.

49:29.375 --> 49:33.207
Okay, well, um, I should go.

49:33.208 --> 49:40.166
(MUSIC PLAYING)

49:41.709 --> 49:43.749
Heather.

49:43.750 --> 49:47.958
(MUSIC PLAYING)

49:47.959 --> 49:50.708
I hope you find
what you're looking for.

49:50.709 --> 49:53.708
(SOFT MUSIC)

49:53.709 --> 50:00.625
(MUSIC PLAYING)

50:05.750 --> 50:09.374
I think it's working, Dave.
What'd I tell you, Roberto?

50:09.375 --> 50:11.833
We're seeing
an increase in customers.

50:11.834 --> 50:14.124
Just need to make
some more calls,

50:14.125 --> 50:15.916
remind them of our
referral discounts,

50:15.917 --> 50:17.499
our money-back guarantees.

50:17.500 --> 50:20.249
Yup, got to do that.
Wilson Family Movers ll be

50:20.250 --> 50:23.499
a thing of the past soon enough.

50:23.500 --> 50:26.541
(UPBEAT ROCK MUSIC)

50:26.542 --> 50:31.457
(MUSIC PLAYING)

50:31.458 --> 50:33.457
(GROANS)

50:33.458 --> 50:39.791
(MUSIC PLAYING)

50:39.792 --> 50:42.750
(TIRES SCREECHING)

50:45.000 --> 50:46.499
I am so sorry, you guys.

50:46.500 --> 50:49.165
I shut my phone off last night,
and the alarm didn't go off.

50:49.166 --> 50:52.124
I-I came as soon as I woke up.

50:52.125 --> 50:53.749
We can see that.
Okay, it's fine.

50:53.750 --> 50:55.457
Let's just get going, okay?

50:55.458 --> 50:57.124
You sure you don't
want to change?

50:57.125 --> 50:58.708
Oh, no, no, no, no, it's fine.
This is important.

50:58.709 --> 51:01.958
Um, I'll just meet
you guys there.

51:01.959 --> 51:03.917
Yeah, all right.

51:08.125 --> 51:09.249
Not today?

51:09.250 --> 51:10.582
I'm gonna drive her
to Golden Meadows,

51:10.583 --> 51:12.499
see if showing her
the place changes her mind.

51:12.500 --> 51:15.417
All right, well,
we're heading back to the shop.

51:17.583 --> 51:18.874
I can come with you if you want.

51:18.875 --> 51:20.165
I don't think that's such
a good idea.

51:20.166 --> 51:21.666
Well, my Dad wanted us
to work together.

51:21.667 --> 51:25.374
I'm not gonna get in your way.
Plus, we could take my car.

51:25.375 --> 51:28.624
Okay, fine. I'll go get her.

51:28.625 --> 51:31.542
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

51:33.542 --> 51:36.541
(INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

51:36.542 --> 51:40.165
(MUSIC PLAYING)

51:40.166 --> 51:43.749
Scott, how can you do this
to your grandma?

51:43.750 --> 51:45.749
This place is awful.

51:45.750 --> 51:48.499
Grandma.

51:48.500 --> 51:51.040
Sweetheart, why are you
wearing pajamas?

51:51.041 --> 51:53.499
I know, I'm sorry.
It's not appropriate attire...

51:53.500 --> 51:56.082
Oh, no, I love it.

51:56.083 --> 51:58.999
I should wear my nightie
when I go out.

51:59.000 --> 52:02.749
It's great to be comfortable,
don't you think, Scott?

52:02.750 --> 52:04.709
Sure, Grandma.

52:06.750 --> 52:08.374
Grandma, look.

52:08.375 --> 52:10.165
Look, we could make this
really exciting.

52:10.166 --> 52:12.541
We could get you
all new furniture.

52:12.542 --> 52:14.165
Or... or we could
just keep the things

52:14.166 --> 52:15.666
that are most important to you.

52:15.667 --> 52:17.916
Go on.
Okay.

52:17.917 --> 52:22.374
Um, well, the window
gets a decent amount of light,

52:22.375 --> 52:26.249
so we could bring those
beautiful floral curtains in.

52:26.250 --> 52:28.207
Those curtains aren't important.

52:28.208 --> 52:30.207
You could throw them out
for all I care.

52:30.208 --> 52:34.749
Okay, um, the kitchen table
can go somewhere over there.

52:34.750 --> 52:36.916
You can throw that out too.

52:36.917 --> 52:40.332
Those things don't matter.

52:40.333 --> 52:42.582
Then what does matter?

52:42.583 --> 52:46.791
Oh, my pictures, my couch,

52:46.792 --> 52:51.249
my grandmother's coffee table,
my father's chairs.

52:51.250 --> 52:55.833
You know, I'm used to things
just feeling a certain way.

52:55.834 --> 52:58.791
Okay, let's put... let's see,

52:58.792 --> 53:00.499
let's put the couch
against this wall,

53:00.500 --> 53:03.582
right, with the coffee table
around here.

53:03.583 --> 53:05.582
Oh, we could put
your father's chairs

53:05.583 --> 53:07.833
on either side
facing the window.

53:07.834 --> 53:09.416
The desk can go over here
with those beautiful

53:09.417 --> 53:10.417
photographs that you have.

53:10.418 --> 53:12.666
Oh, the side table right there

53:12.667 --> 53:14.958
with that gorgeous lamp
that you have?

53:14.959 --> 53:16.457
And then we could do... oh,

53:16.458 --> 53:20.124
the big, uh, oriental rug
right here, right?

53:20.125 --> 53:22.457
And it would just bring
the whole room together.

53:22.458 --> 53:24.958
You really think
all that would fit?

53:24.959 --> 53:27.874
Not everything.

53:27.875 --> 53:29.792
Just what's most important.

53:36.375 --> 53:40.958
What do you see for the bedroom?

53:40.959 --> 53:43.290
Well, I think we should bring
your bed first.

53:43.291 --> 53:46.166
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

53:49.375 --> 53:53.332
Hey.
Hey.

53:53.333 --> 53:57.999
Thanks for what you did.

53:58.000 --> 54:00.040
Don't mention it.

54:00.041 --> 54:03.833
It's just I have been trying
to move her for so long.

54:03.834 --> 54:07.958
I just never thought to... anyway,

54:07.959 --> 54:09.416
I'm really sorry
about yesterday.

54:09.417 --> 54:10.749
I-I crossed the line.

54:10.750 --> 54:13.457
No, it's okay.
You're right.

54:13.458 --> 54:17.666
I've been really difficult
to work with.

54:17.667 --> 54:19.833
Yeah, I shouldn't have gotten
into your business like that.

54:19.834 --> 54:22.332
Don't be sorry.
What you said?

54:22.333 --> 54:23.624
It was true.

54:23.625 --> 54:27.165
I... I've had these scores
for a couple years,

54:27.166 --> 54:30.124
and for whatever reason I just
haven't had the guts to apply.

54:30.125 --> 54:32.541
You will when
it's the right time.

54:32.542 --> 54:33.958
Yeah, I know.

54:33.959 --> 54:36.457
That's... that's the plan.
I just... I don't know.

54:36.458 --> 54:38.207
I just got to figure out
my next move.

54:38.208 --> 54:43.791
Well, taking steps will move
you in the right direction.

54:43.792 --> 54:44.916
Moving puns.

54:44.917 --> 54:46.874
So I guess my Dad
taught you those?

54:46.875 --> 54:49.791
He certainly did.
(CHUCKLES)

54:49.792 --> 54:51.708
You know,
my Mom was the mastermind,

54:51.709 --> 54:54.791
but my Dad and I,
we caught on pretty quickly.

54:54.792 --> 54:59.374
(CHUCKLES) Yeah.

54:59.375 --> 55:01.457
All right, I think
we should head back.

55:01.458 --> 55:02.708
Yeah, yeah.

55:02.709 --> 55:04.082
Um, hey, a couple of us

55:04.083 --> 55:06.582
are going to Brandy
Rose Tavern tonight.

55:06.583 --> 55:08.124
Uh, do you want to go?

55:08.125 --> 55:11.708
If you don't have
any paperwork or organization.

55:11.709 --> 55:14.374
Oh, um...
You don't have to go.

55:14.375 --> 55:16.165
I was just extending
an invitation.

55:16.166 --> 55:19.082
You know what?
I'd love to.

55:19.083 --> 55:22.666
Cool, but you may want
to change out of the pajamas

55:22.667 --> 55:25.583
because that place
isn't that casual.

55:29.417 --> 55:33.374
You know, I read
that Venus is in retrograde.

55:33.375 --> 55:36.165
(CHUCKLES)
And what does that mean?

55:36.166 --> 55:39.332
I have no idea.
I don't know. I don't know.

55:39.333 --> 55:42.124
I skim some woman magazine

55:42.125 --> 55:44.874
in the line of the grocery store
from time to time.

55:44.875 --> 55:47.582
Wh... why?

55:47.583 --> 55:50.874
Just so I-I can understand
you better.

55:50.875 --> 55:53.416
You don't have to read
a magazine to understand me.

55:53.417 --> 55:56.541
You just have to ask.

55:56.542 --> 55:59.624
Okay, then, here goes.

55:59.625 --> 56:02.958
What is it that
I should know about you?

56:02.959 --> 56:06.874
That I care very much about you,

56:06.875 --> 56:10.082
but I don't want
to be kept a secret.

56:10.083 --> 56:13.082
Hmm, that conversation again.

56:13.083 --> 56:16.165
Hey, that's not fair.

56:16.166 --> 56:19.290
We're gonna have to deal
with this sooner or later.

56:19.291 --> 56:23.290
We... we've been
going out six months.

56:23.291 --> 56:25.666
I'm starting to think
I embarrass you.

56:25.667 --> 56:28.290
No, that...
that is not how it is.

56:28.291 --> 56:29.541
I... you know what?

56:29.542 --> 56:32.416
I promise, I will tell Olivia
right when we get back.

56:32.417 --> 56:33.666
I... it's just that Olivia

56:33.667 --> 56:36.290
and her Mom have
always been two peas in a pod,

56:36.291 --> 56:39.708
and I-I just don't know
how she's gonna react

56:39.709 --> 56:42.833
when she finds out I'm in love
with another woman.

56:42.834 --> 56:47.833
You're in love with me?
(ROMANTIC MUSIC)

56:47.834 --> 56:49.874
Yes.

56:49.875 --> 56:51.834
That's nice.

56:57.709 --> 57:00.708
(LIGHT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

57:00.709 --> 57:07.667
(MUSIC PLAYING)

57:13.500 --> 57:15.999
Can you guys just set that
right there in the center?

57:16.000 --> 57:19.124
Thanks.

57:19.125 --> 57:23.290
All right. I think that...
I think that works.

57:23.291 --> 57:24.916
All right, coming through here.

57:24.917 --> 57:27.708
Wow.

57:27.709 --> 57:31.040
Oh, this is great.

57:31.041 --> 57:33.249
You did such a great job.
Yeah, it's really good.

57:33.250 --> 57:34.250
Craig and I are gonna head
to the truck,

57:34.251 --> 57:36.666
see if we left anything behind.

57:36.667 --> 57:38.583
All right.

57:40.500 --> 57:42.499
Okay, let's see.

57:42.500 --> 57:47.541
(MUSIC PLAYING)

57:47.542 --> 57:48.749
All right.

57:48.750 --> 57:52.708
Oh, wow, look at this.

57:52.709 --> 57:53.999
That's my Dad.

57:54.000 --> 57:57.499
Oh, he looks just like you.

57:57.500 --> 57:58.916
Ah, that's what everybody says.

57:58.917 --> 58:01.290
The Norrell genes are strong.

58:01.291 --> 58:03.249
Is this your aunt?

58:03.250 --> 58:06.165
Yeah, that's Auntie Nolene.
Nolene Norrell?

58:06.166 --> 58:07.833
Norrell, yes, I know.

58:07.834 --> 58:09.290
When I was a little girl my Mom

58:09.291 --> 58:11.374
and I would spend hours

58:11.375 --> 58:15.290
rearranging the furniture
in the dollhouse.

58:15.291 --> 58:19.290
I know it's just my imagination,
but I could have sworn the dolls

58:19.291 --> 58:21.582
were so happy
when I redecorated their rooms.

58:21.583 --> 58:23.416
(CHUCKLES)

58:23.417 --> 58:27.916
Since then it's been
my dream to design.

58:27.917 --> 58:33.290
Well, I think your Mom would
be very proud of you right now.

58:33.291 --> 58:36.874
Well...

58:36.875 --> 58:38.750
would you look at this?

58:43.917 --> 58:47.749
It's lovely, simply lovely.

58:47.750 --> 58:49.457
Mm.

58:49.458 --> 58:51.874
It's definitely
not your house, but we wanted

58:51.875 --> 58:55.332
to make it feel like a home.

58:55.333 --> 58:57.332
It's perfect.

58:57.333 --> 59:01.624
(CHUCKLES)

59:01.625 --> 59:02.958
Oh.

59:02.959 --> 59:07.040
Oh, get in here, Scott.

59:07.041 --> 59:09.541
Mm. Oh.

59:09.542 --> 59:12.124
Thank you.

59:12.125 --> 59:15.666
Hey, what you did for my grandma
today, it was just incredible.

59:15.667 --> 59:18.791
Oh, don't worry about it.
It's simple staging.

59:18.792 --> 59:20.165
Yeah, but I could
totally see it.

59:20.166 --> 59:21.708
I could tell you're really
good at your job.

59:21.709 --> 59:25.499
Well, my boss... my former boss

59:25.500 --> 59:27.457
says my work has no heart.

59:27.458 --> 59:28.958
Well, then change her mind,
you know?

59:28.959 --> 59:30.332
Show her what you're made of.

59:30.333 --> 59:32.082
We all have room
for improvement.

59:32.083 --> 59:34.332
I know.

59:34.333 --> 59:36.457
(SIGHS)
Is Heather coming?

59:36.458 --> 59:39.791
No, no.

59:39.792 --> 59:41.165
We actually broke up.

59:41.166 --> 59:44.124
Oh, I'm so sorry.
No, no, no, it... it's okay.

59:44.125 --> 59:45.499
She's great.

59:45.500 --> 59:50.082
It's just, you know,
we both want different things.

59:50.083 --> 59:52.582
Hey, do you want go play pool?

59:52.583 --> 59:57.040
If you're lucky, I may,
I may actually let you win.

59:57.041 --> 59:58.416
You don't have to worry
about it, Scott.

59:58.417 --> 01:00:01.666
(WHISPERS)
I always win.

01:00:01.667 --> 01:00:05.332
Now, there's that
competitive spirit.

01:00:05.333 --> 01:00:08.416
We call next game.
Oh, you got it, man.

01:00:08.417 --> 01:00:09.833
Hey, guys.
Hey.

01:00:09.834 --> 01:00:12.207
Who's your friend?
Oh, right, sorry.

01:00:12.208 --> 01:00:13.208
This is Jesse.

01:00:13.209 --> 01:00:15.165
Hey.
Hey, Jesse, Scott.

01:00:15.166 --> 01:00:17.708
Nice to meet you, Scott, guys.

01:00:17.709 --> 01:00:20.625
All right, we're gonna have
a drink.

01:00:22.542 --> 01:00:25.416
All right, pass me the balls.

01:00:25.417 --> 01:00:27.374
(INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

01:00:27.375 --> 01:00:29.499
Guys, I told my Dad
I would fix this,

01:00:29.500 --> 01:00:33.207
and the calendar
is still completely empty.

01:00:33.208 --> 01:00:35.374
You know, I've been thinking.

01:00:35.375 --> 01:00:38.999
I was thinking about
the awesome job that you did,

01:00:39.000 --> 01:00:41.624
also what you said
about finding an advantage,

01:00:41.625 --> 01:00:44.207
and I think our advantage
is you.

01:00:44.208 --> 01:00:46.249
What do you mean?
What you did for my grandma,

01:00:46.250 --> 01:00:48.874
the staging and redesigning
of the space,

01:00:48.875 --> 01:00:51.207
I mean, that's something that
Acme could never offer.

01:00:51.208 --> 01:00:54.374
Sure, yes, we may need
to compete pricewise,

01:00:54.375 --> 01:00:58.416
but we have a person
that can create a new home.

01:00:58.417 --> 01:00:59.749
Yeah, that's... that's good.

